Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: large hall

A large hall spreads out before you. The deep burgundy colors of the room provide an inviting, warm atmosphere. Five tables are scattered about which are set to view the stage to the north. The stage itself extends the length of the northern wall, flanked by two red velvet curtains which can be drawn open or closed. Situated in the southwest corner is a bar with several stools surrounding it. The bar appears to be well-stocked with dozens of liquor bottles in all shapes and sizes. You also note a crystal chandelier hanging from the high arched ceiling. There are tall exotic maple double doors to the south and a simple maple door to the northwest.
A large hall decorated with deep burgundy hues with a stage to the north. There are double doors to the south and a door to the northwest.

A large hall decorated with contrasting deep burgundy fabrics and light maple wood. A brightly-lit stage extends the length of the northern wall. A bar stocked with dozens of liquor bottles stands in the southwest corner of the room. Several tables are scattered about. You also note a crystal chandelier hanging from the high arched ceiling. There are tall exotic maple double doors to the south and a simple maple door to the northwest.

the bottles of liquor
A wide variety of glass bottles in all shapes, sizes, and colors stand on the shelves behind the serving counter.
the high arched ceiling

A high arched ceiling made of varnished maple. Evenly-spaced maple buttresses carved with an elaborate floral pattern extend from the upper portions of the walls to support the high ceiling, forming a geometric criss-cross network above your head. There is a glimmering crystal chandelier hanging from here.

glimmering crystal chandelier

A glimmering crystal chandelier hangs from the high arched ceiling. Thousands of tiny faceted crystals hang in circular tiers, each smaller than the last until they converge into a single, larger crystal. The crystals sparkle in a myriad of colors as they catch the light from the surrounding area.
maple serving counter

A semi-circular serving counter crafted of varnished maple wood stands in the southwest corner of the room, restricting access to the liquor bottles. The surface of the counter has been sanded and polished smooth. A thin, upholstered black leather pad covers the outside edge. Six high-back maple barstools are standing in front of the counter.
the elegant red velvet curtains

The elegant red velvet curtains reach from ceiling to floor, providing a dark backdrop for the large stage. The curtains can be drawn open in the center to allow performers to pass through to the backstage area.
the burgundy carpeted floor
The floor is covered with a burgundy carpet with a short, stiff pile which is easily cleaned.
The floor is covered with plush burgundy carpet.
the shelves of liquor bottles
Several polished maple shelves behind the maple serving counter bearing dozens of glass bottles of all shapes, sizes, and colors.
large, curved maple stage

The large wooden stage runs the length of the northern wall in a semicircular shape. It consists of raised maple planks which have been sanded smoothly and then varnished to give the stage a sleek appearance. Two red velvet curtains provide a solid backdrop for performers.
The large, curved wooden stage running the length of the northern wall is made of raised, smoothly-sanded maple planks which have been varnished to create a sleek, flat surface for performers.

the eastern wall

The eastern wall is made up of unfinished wooden planks. A covering of burgundy velvet has been attached and pleated at regular intervals to prevent echoing inside of the hall.
